sec.p:
To determine the start medium composition of S1 and S2, a non-linear solver technique was performed using Microsoft Excel [4,8]. This was calculated with the following constrictions:
All fractions of LF, NDNE, and water are greater than zero;
The sum of all fractions of LF, NDNE, and water equals 100%;
The total N and P contents of the final mixture should be below the limits proposed for Lemna minor to obtain optimal growth [9];
The N/P ratio of the medium should equal 7.4, as this is the ratio between the N removal and P removal that was determined in an outdoor duckweed system with diluted NDNE as the growing medium [4].
